rdf:Description.lla:note: Notes in Log Book say that he was taken to New Providence Asylum on 14 April and died of consumption there the following day.
Note on page 8 of the Log Book that John Evans became ill with Yellow Fever while in St. George's, Bermuda but recovered and returned to his post.
Note on page 9 of the Log Book that Rees Griffiths died of Yellow Fever in hospital at St. George's, Bermuda on 06 September 1864.
Note on page 11 of the Log Book that Richard Williams died, on board the ship, of Yellow Fever at St. George's, Bermuda on 05 September 1864.
Note on page 12 of the Log Book that Frederick Brandt was taken to hospital at St. George's, Bermuda with fever and recovered. He returned to the ship, in apparent good health, on 09 September 1864.
Note on page 10 of the Log Book that John Evans was taken ill, on 31 August 1864, with Yellow Fever at St. George's, Bermuda. A nurse attended him and he recovered.
Note on page 14 of the Log Book that William Clark died of Yellow Fever in hospital at St. George's, Bermuda on 09 September 1864.
Note on page 18 of the Log Book that James Downie was taken to hospital at St. George's, Bermuda with fever, recovered and returned to the ship on 16 September 1864.
Note on page 18 of the Log Book that Daniel Sweeney was taken to hospital at St. George's, Bermuda with fever, recovered and returned to the ship on 15 September 1864.
